# Binary test fixtures (zlib-compressed vanilla game tables). Mark them binary
# so git never applies EOL normalization and always renders them as binary in
# diffs. Without this, a tiny zlib blob that happens to contain no NUL byte is
# misdetected as text -- shown as a garbage "text" diff on GitHub, and at risk
# of CRLF corruption on checkout under core.autocrlf, which would silently
# break the fixture (it would no longer decompress).
*.zlib binary
